      • readEmbeddingFileTxt

        public static Map<String,float[]> readEmbeddingFileTxt(File file,
                                                       boolean hasHeader)
                                                throws IOException
        Read an embeddings file in text format.

        If hasHeader is set to true, the first line is expected to contain the size and dimensionality of the vectors. This is typically true for files generated by Word2Vec (in text format).

        Parameters:
        file - the input file
        hasHeader - if true, read size and dimensionality from the first line
        Returns:
        a Map<String, float[]> mapping each token to a vector.
        Throws:
        IOException - if the input file cannot be read
        See Also:
        readEmbeddingFileTxt(InputStream, boolean)

      • readEmbeddingFileTxt

        public static Map<String,float[]> readEmbeddingFileTxt(InputStream inputStream,
                                                       boolean hasHeader)
                                                throws IOException
        Read embeddings in text format from an InputStream. Each line is expected to have a whitespace-separated list <token> <value1> <value2> ....
        Parameters:
        inputStream - an InputStream
        hasHeader - if true, read size and dimensionality from the first line
        Returns:
        a Map<String, float[]> mapping each token to a vector.
        Throws:
        IOException - if the input file cannot be read

      • convertMalletEmbeddingsToBinary

        public static void convertMalletEmbeddingsToBinary(File malletEmbeddings,
                                                   boolean aCaseless,
                                                   Locale aLocale,
                                                   File targetFile)
                                            throws IOException
        Read a (compressed) Mallet embeddings file (in text format) and convert it into the binary format using BinaryWordVectorUtils.
        Parameters:
        malletEmbeddings - a File holding embeddings in text format
        aCaseless - if true, all input tokens are expected to be caseless
        aLocale - the Locale to use
        targetFile - the output File
        Throws:
        IOException - if an I/O error occurs.
